The Obsidian Spire stood at the heart of Aethelgard Academy, a monolithic tower of dark, mana-conductive stone that seemed to pierce the very clouds. For the students, it was the ultimate proving ground. To the public, it was a spectacle. To Cian, it was a cage where he had to perform without showing his true teeth.
The exam was simple: reach the 10th floor. The higher the floor, the denser the mana and the more aggressive the simulated monsters.
Chapter 4: The Obsidian Spire
"Nervous?" Lyra asked, checking the tension on her recurve bow. She wore a sleek, white-and-gold combat suit that shimmered with protective enchantments.
Cian adjusted his black academy jacket. He felt the heavy presence of Vanguard 01 resting within his literal shadow, a cold weight that no one else could perceive. "Just focused. Remember the plan, Lyra. You take the lead. I’m just the support."
"The 'Dormant' kid playing bodyguard for the Sun Heiress," she teased, though her eyes were serious. "The proctors are watching via the scrying orbs. If you do anything... weird... they’ll notice."
"I’ll be careful."
[QUEST START: REACH THE 10TH FLOOR]
Reward: 500 Gold, +2 Skill Points.
Hidden Objective: Secure the Top Rank for Lyra Valerius without revealing the Void Monarch class.
The massive iron gates of the Spire groaned open. Fifty pairs of students rushed inside.
By the 5th floor, the "simulations" turned deadly. The walls of the Spire bled out Iron-Husk Beetles—monsters with shells as hard as granite. Most students were slowing down, their mana pools draining.
"They're too thick!" Lyra shouted, firing an explosive fire arrow that only cracked the shell of a lead beetle. "I can't pierce the joints fast enough!"
Cian stepped into her shadow, his hand hovering just above the ground. Vanguard, go.
He didn't summon the shadow soldier fully. Instead, he channeled the skill [Shadow Extension]. Beneath the beetle’s feet, the floor turned into a pitch-black liquid. Tiny, spectral hands—extensions of his soldier—reached up and gripped the beetle’s legs, pinning it in place.
"Now! The underbelly!" Cian called out.
Lyra didn't hesitate. She let loose a stream of arrows, the fire blooming like roses against the beetle’s soft tissue. It shattered into pixels of light.
To the orbs watching from the outside, it looked like the beetle had simply stumbled.
Up on the 9th floor, the air was thick with the scent of ozone. Only three teams remained: Lyra and Cian, and two teams from the High Houses of Thorne and Draken.
"Look at them," sneered Kaelen Draken, a high-ranking Spear-user. "The fire-girl and the charity case. How did you even get this high, Thorne? Piggybacking off her mana?"
Cian didn't answer. He was looking at the ceiling. The 10th floor wasn't a simulation. The mana sensors were screaming.
[WARNING: SYSTEM INTERFERENCE DETECTED]
The Spire’s Mana Core has been corrupted.
Boss Spawn: [Obsidian Sentinel - Rank D+ (Berserk)]
A massive golem of black crystal dropped from the ceiling, crashing between the teams. It wasn't the training dummy it was supposed to be. Its eyes burned with a chaotic, red light, and it swung a fist the size of a boulder.
Kaelen Draken was sent flying into a wall, his spear snapping like a toothpick.
"Cian, the exits are locked!" Lyra cried, her flames turning white-hot as she tried to melt the Sentinel’s arm. "The mana core is overloading!"
Cian saw the proctors frantically trying to shut down the tower through the scrying orbs, but the "Berserk" status meant the system was locked. He looked at Lyra. She was exhausted, her mana battery flickering.
He had to act, but he couldn't let the orbs see.
"Lyra, blind them!" Cian commanded.
"What?"
"Use your Nova Flare! Blinding light, five seconds! Do it now!"
Trusting him implicitly, Lyra closed her eyes and released a radial explosion of pure, golden radiance. The scrying orbs turned white, the feed cut by the sheer intensity of the light.
In those five seconds, Cian let the darkness out.
"Extraction: Full Manifestation!"
Vanguard 01 erupted from Cian’s shadow, now towering eight feet tall and clad in violet-tinted plate armor. The shadow soldier leaped, its ethereal blade slicing through the Sentinel’s crystal neck like it was dry parchment.
[BOSS DEFEATED]
Experience Gained... LEVEL UP!
Level: 9
As the light faded, the Sentinel lay in pieces. Cian stood there, breathing hard, his shadow soldier already tucked back into his feet. He looked like he was simply catching his breath.
When the orbs regained focus, they saw Lyra standing over the core of the boss, and Cian leaning against a pillar.
The intercom crackled. The Headmaster’s voice was filled with disbelief. "Floor 10 cleared. Team Valerius... takes first place."
Lyra turned to Cian, her face pale. She had seen the silhouette in the light. She knew.
"That thing," she whispered, walking toward him. "That wasn't a skill, Cian. That was a living shadow."
Cian wiped a smudge of soot from his cheek. "It’s our secret, remember?"
